<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Evade ( clicking hide in combat ) is not a seperate skill or at least i have not noticed it to go up.  Evade has also only worked for me in a group.  It will work solo but not like it is supposed to.  Evade is the opposite of taunt.  It will make you go down on the mobs aggro list.  Thus turning the mob from you and giving an open shot at a backstab.  To evade effectively this is what I do.  First i click sneak to be able to move while hidden.  Then click hide.  You might evade combat or you might fail.  if you do evade properly the moster should immediatly turn from you and face the next most damaging party member.  Then you backstab. Uh-oh the mob is back on you now.  Wait 5 secs till hide button comes back up and repeat instructions.  This seems to work especially well with a taunting class on the other side of the mob.  It will make it work more often than not.  Hope all this helps</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
