<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Here are the true facts as opposed to the insaniacs about evade. This is part of your hide skill and your ability to evade is tied directly to your hide level. It only works in a group so be careful-you can never hide when a MoB is aggroing you alone. You can, in a group battle, take a step back, stand totaly still and stop attacking, then hit your hide hot key. You will get the screen message "you have sucessfully ducked away from the main combat" (if it works, of course!). This will lower your aggro level and the MoB will go after someone else, not you! Evade will give you a break, especially if you are near death and can't run, and prolly save your life. Also, evade can be used tactically to really take maximum advantage of backstab, if, along with sneak, you evade, then sneak behind the MoB, you can keep backstabbing and not get hit. I have found that this works well with vey hard hitting MoBs like Sand Gaints. I do not like taking hits for 100 plus damage but sometimes it is worth it if you can pickpocket a Giant! I did this recently with Cazel, the level 55 SG in Oasis, for 28pp, and lived!<hr>Penny</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
